In addition, Kovalchuk raised the issue of responsibility for the development of natural technologies, as well as told about the risks that inevitably arise when creating such technologies.
“The advent of such technologies is a unique thing, it’s a tremendous good.
This is the explosive growth of medical technologies, it is the improvement of quality of life and infrastructure.
But there is also the other side.
The development of nature-like technologies is, in fact, a technological reproduction of systems of living nature.
There is a reverse side - a targeted intervention in a person's life activities.
There are always risks.
There was a car, and people were dying under the wheels.
The cars are still in use.
The dual nature of technology immediately.
I am creating medical new technology, and at the same time I can create weapons of mass destruction," REN TV quoted the scientist as saying.
After watching the film and discussing modern scientific breakthroughs, the students were able to ask questions to the participants of the meeting.
In the role of the speakers were the candidate of physical and mathematical sciences, the head of the Kurchatov complex of NBICS-nature-like technologies of NIC "Kurchatov Institute" Yulia Dyakov and the head of the Kurchatov complex of NBICS-technology Vyacheslav Demin.
