The Ministry of Finance of the Russian Federation predicted the course of the ruble for 17 years ahead
The Ministry of Finance of Russia expects a gradual weakening of the ruble rate - up to 73.9 rubles. for the dollar by 2031-2035, follows from the draft long-term budget forecast, submitted to the State Duma together with the draft federal budget.
In 2021-2025 the ruble rate, according to the forecast, will be 66.4 rubles per dollar, in 2026-2030 - 71.1 rubles, and in the next five years - 73.9.
The Office notes that these figures are the nominal rate.
The real effective exchange rate (the indicator that takes into account the changes in the exchange rates of countries that are the main trading partners of the Russian Federation) will remain stable, officials say.
As for inflation, by 2020 it will be 3.5%, and then stabilized at about 4%, according to the Ministry of Finance.
